"{\"uid\": \"timesofmalta.com-article-olympics-controversy-judge-according-appearance-french-embassy.1096055\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"The French embassy has reacted to dismay in some quarters over a scene in the Olympics opening ceremony seen as mocking the Last Supper, quoting the artistic producer saying that was not what was being depicted.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 211, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4, \"end\": 10, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.8965071289284416, \"rank\": 0.11316837275278666, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some quarters\", \"from\": 44, \"to\": 57}, {\"ngram\": \"a scene\", \"from\": 63, \"to\": 70}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics opening ceremony\", \"from\": 74, \"to\": 103}, {\"ngram\": \"the Last Supper\", \"from\": 120, \"to\": 135}, {\"ngram\": \"the artistic producer\", \"from\": 145, \"to\": 166}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The conference of French bishops, as well as Malta's Archbishop Charles Scicluna were among thosewho condemned the scene.\", \"from\": 213, \"to\": 334, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 231, \"end\": 237, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.8965071289284416, \"rank\": 0.11316837275278666, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 258, \"end\": 263, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malta\", \"score\": 0.9999227723949108, \"rank\": 7.355752068979417e-05, \"text\": \"Malta\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malta\"}, {\"begin\": 266, \"end\": 276, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\", \"score\": 0.9994584239161038, \"rank\": 0.0005293803016565067, \"text\": \"Archbishop\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\"}, {\"begin\": 277, \"end\": 293, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_Scicluna\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Charles Scicluna\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_Scicluna\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_Scicluna\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The conference\", \"from\": 213, \"to\": 227}, {\"ngram\": \"thosewho\", \"from\": 305, \"to\": 313}, {\"ngram\": \"the scene\", \"from\": 324, \"to\": 333}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The archbishop even urged the public to write to the French ambassador in Malta to raise their objections.\", \"from\": 336, \"to\": 442, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 389, \"end\": 395, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.8965071289284416, \"rank\": 0.11316837275278666, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 410, \"end\": 415, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malta\", \"score\": 0.9999227723949108, \"rank\": 7.355752068979417e-05, \"text\": \"Malta\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malta\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The archbishop\", \"from\": 336, \"to\": 350}, {\"ngram\": \"the public\", \"from\": 362, \"to\": 372}, {\"ngram\": \"their objections\", \"from\": 425, \"to\": 441}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a statement, the French embassy said it was sorry that Christians felt offended by the dinner scene where some believed they detected a parody of the Last Supper.\", \"from\": 444, \"to\": 609, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 464, \"end\": 470, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.8965071289284416, \"rank\": 0.11316837275278666, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 502, \"end\": 512, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9892863606060281, \"rank\": 0.010665178552646488, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a statement\", \"from\": 447, \"to\": 458}, {\"ngram\": \"the dinner scene\", \"from\": 530, \"to\": 546}, {\"ngram\": \"a parody\", \"from\": 581, \"to\": 589}, {\"ngram\": \"the Last Supper\", \"from\": 593, \"to\": 608}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The embassy added a quote from St John saying: \\\"Judge not according to the appearance, but judge righteous judgment\\\".\", \"from\": 611, \"to\": 728, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The embassy\", \"from\": 611, \"to\": 622}, {\"ngram\": \"a quote\", \"from\": 629, \"to\": 636}, {\"ngram\": \"St John\", \"from\": 642, \"to\": 649}, {\"ngram\": \"the appearance\", \"from\": 682, \"to\": 696}, {\"ngram\": \"righteous judgment\", \"from\": 708, \"to\": 726}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The embassy then quoted the ceremony's artistic director explaining how the scene did not depict the Last Supper at all.\", \"from\": 732, \"to\": 852, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The embassy\", \"from\": 732, \"to\": 743}, {\"ngram\": \"the ceremony's artistic director\", \"from\": 756, \"to\": 788}, {\"ngram\": \"the scene\", \"from\": 804, \"to\": 813}, {\"ngram\": \"the Last Supper\", \"from\": 829, \"to\": 844}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"So no, it wasn't my inspiration.\", \"from\": 854, \"to\": 887, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my inspiration\", \"from\": 872, \"to\": 886}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In fact, I think it was quite clear that Dionysus was coming to the table.\", \"from\": 888, \"to\": 962, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 929, \"end\": 937, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.549994721048765e-18, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"fact\", \"from\": 891, \"to\": 895}, {\"ngram\": \"the table\", \"from\": 952, \"to\": 961}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Why Dionysus?\", \"from\": 963, \"to\": 976, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Why Dionysus\", \"from\": 963, \"to\": 975}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Because he is first and foremost the god of celebration in Greek mythology, and the painting is called \\\"Les Festivit\\u00e9s\\\".\", \"from\": 977, \"to\": 1097, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1036, \"end\": 1051, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"score\": 0.9999998883604411, \"rank\": 1.1163955364369925e-07, \"text\": \"Greek mythology\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the god\", \"from\": 1010, \"to\": 1017}, {\"ngram\": \"celebration\", \"from\": 1021, \"to\": 1032}, {\"ngram\": \"the painting\", \"from\": 1057, \"to\": 1069}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"Les Festivit\\u00e9s\", \"from\": 1080, \"to\": 1095}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He is the god of wine, an important symbol in France, and the father of Sequana, the goddess linked to the river Seine.\", \"from\": 1098, \"to\": 1217, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1144, \"end\": 1150, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"score\": 0.671965230993276, \"rank\": 0.4869620316605027, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 1170, \"end\": 1177, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sequana\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sequana\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sequana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sequana\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the god\", \"from\": 1104, \"to\": 1111}, {\"ngram\": \"wine\", \"from\": 1115, \"to\": 1119}, {\"ngram\": \"an important symbol\", \"from\": 1121, \"to\": 1140}, {\"ngram\": \"the father\", \"from\": 1156, \"to\": 1166}, {\"ngram\": \"the goddess\", \"from\": 1179, \"to\": 1190}, {\"ngram\": \"the river Seine\", \"from\": 1201, \"to\": 1216}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(...) You will never find in me any desire to mock or denigrate.\", \"from\": 1218, \"to\": 1282, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"any desire\", \"from\": 1250, \"to\": 1260}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I wanted to organise a ceremony that would repair and reconcile, and that would reaffirm the values of our Republic: liberty, equality and fraternity\\\".\", \"from\": 1283, \"to\": 1434, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a ceremony\", \"from\": 1304, \"to\": 1314}, {\"ngram\": \"the values\", \"from\": 1372, \"to\": 1382}, {\"ngram\": \"our Republic\", \"from\": 1386, \"to\": 1398}, {\"ngram\": \"liberty\", \"from\": 1400, \"to\": 1407}, {\"ngram\": \"equality\", \"from\": 1409, \"to\": 1417}, {\"ngram\": \"fraternity\", \"from\": 1422, \"to\": 1432}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The embassy said France was proud of its heritage and patrimony: it watched in horror as the cathedral of Notre-Dame in Paris burned down, and is following with emotion the stages of its reconstruction.\", \"from\": 1436, \"to\": 1638, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1453, \"end\": 1459, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"score\": 0.671965230993276, \"rank\": 0.4869620316605027, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\":